<br>
All said and done they attempted Ragefire and got wiped out. Sorry but go to the end of the line.<br>
<br>
Also here is a hint on keeping massive Mobs from despawning in the future.<br>
<br>
When you engage a large scale type mob and fail to kill him - designate someone - even a naked someone to run in and &quot;Kite&quot; the mob - yes it will mean this person will probably die at some point,  get them help - keep a few bards or Druids handy and engage the mob from time time to time to keep them from DESPAWNING!!! Engaged mobs don't despawn and even at the cost of a death engaging a mob and dieing resets the despawn timer.<br>
<br>
While you have 2 or 3 different folks concentrating completely on keeping the mob pissed so it doesn't poof - regroup - ress - buff and engage as soon as possible.<br>
<br>
I will not guarentee this to work everytime, but time is of the essance in situations like this.<br>
<br>
But again all said and done, with the amount of time involved in this camp it isn't right to tell the rest of the server &quot;Oops we screwed up, thanks for waiting another 7 days for us to try it again&quot;<br>
<br>
Obviously if there was some way we could prove you failed because you were maliciously trained by individuals bent on your failure we would fully support giving them a second chance and we would ride the two that allegadly did this out on a rail.<br>
